{
  "local_port": 56876,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I link my valid Aadhaar card to the SBI?",
  "response": "To link your valid Aadhaar card to your State Bank of India (SBI) account, you can follow these steps:\n\n### Online Method:\n1. **Visit the SBI Website**: Go to the official SBI website at www.sbi.co.in.\n2. **Log in to Internet Banking**: Click on \"Personal Banking\" and log in using your username and password.\n3. **Navigate to 'My Accounts'**: After logging in, go to the \"My Accounts\" section.\n4. **Select 'Link Your Aadhaar'**: Under the \"My Accounts\" section, you will find an option called \"Link Your Aadhaar\". Click on it.\n5. **Enter Details**: Enter your account number, Aadhaar number, and the Captcha code as prompted.\n6. **Submit**: Click on the \"Submit\" button. You will receive a confirmation message that your Aadhaar has been linked to your SBI account.\n\n### Offline Method:\n1. **Visit an SBI Branch**: Go to your nearest SBI branch.\n2. **Fill Out the Form**: Ask for the Aadhaar linking form and fill it out with your details.\n3. **Submit Documents**: Submit the filled form along with a photocopy of your Aadhaar card to the bank officials.\n4. **Acknowledgment**: You will receive an acknowledgment that your Aadhaar has been submitted for linking.\n\n### Through SMS:\n1. **Compose SMS**: Open your SMS app and type the message in the following format: UID <space> Aadhaar Number <space> Account Number.\n2. **Send SMS**: Send the SMS to 567676 from your registered mobile number.\n\n### Through ATM:\n1. **Visit an SBI ATM**: Go to the nearest SBI ATM.\n2. **Insert Debit Card**: Insert your SBI debit card and enter your PIN.\n3. **Select 'Services'**: From the main menu, select \"Services\".\n4. **Choose 'Aadhaar Linking'**: From the \"Services\" menu, select \"Aadhaar Linking\".\n5. **Enter Details**: Enter your Aadhaar number and confirm the linking.\n\n### Additional Notes:\n- Ensure that the mobile number registered with your Aadhaar is the same as the one registered with your SBI account for seamless linking.\n- If you encounter any issues, you can contact SBI customer care at 1800 1234 or 1800 2100 for assistance.\n\nBy following these methods, you should be able to link your Aadhaar card to your SBI account successfully.",
